    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> into thin discs (roughly the thickness of a \u00a31 coin)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bolognese-x-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato discs</strong> to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Sprinkle with<strong> cold water </strong>(this will help the potatoes cook through!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until softened and slightly golden</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bolognese-x-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bolognese-x-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and<strong> chopped tomato</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bolognese-x-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Once the onions and tomatoes have began to soften, add your <strong>mince</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min further or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bolognese-x-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pan with your<strong> beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, bring to the boil and cook for 4-5 min further or until thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>bolognese sauce</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>double cream</strong> with the <strong>remaining garlic </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> garlic cream</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bolognese-x-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, transfer the <strong>bolognese sauce</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (or use individual ones for fancy presentation) and top with layers of the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong></p><p>Pour the <strong>garlic cream</strong> all over</p><p>Sprinkle over the<strong> grated cheese</strong> with<strong> </strong>a pinch of<strong> black pepper </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>bolognese x</strong> <strong>dauphinoise potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bolognese-x-dauphinoise-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> salad </strong>with a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>bolognese x</strong> <strong>dauphinoise potatoes </strong>with the <strong>dressed salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
